== 目标与职能 ==
===目标 ===
根据1993年颁布实施之《新中央银行法》之第1章第1款第3条<ref>{{harvnb|《The New Central Bank Act(RA 7653)》|1993|loc=Chapter I：Article I：Section 3}}{{quote|''Responsibility and Primary Objective.'' _ The Bangko Sentral shall provide policy directions in the areas of money, banking, and credit. It shall have supervision over the operations of banks and exercise such regulatory powers as provided in this Act and other pertinent laws over the operations of finance companies and non-bank financial institutions performing quasi-banking functions, hereafter referred to as quasi- banks, and institutions performing similar functions.<br /> The primary objective of the Bangko Sentral is to maintain price stability conducive to a balanced and sustainable growth of the economy. It shall also promote and maintain monetary stability and the convertibility of the peso.}}</ref>，菲律宾中央银行之法定目标为保持[[物价|物价]]稳定，维护[[货币|货币]]之稳定及可兑换性，以促进经济的均衡与[[可持续发展|可持续发展]]。<ref name="Functions">{{Cite web|url=http://www.bsp.gov.ph/about/functions.asp|title=Overview of Functions and Operations|accessdate=2014-07-05|author=|last=|first=|authorlink=|coauthors=|date=|year=|month=|format=|work=|publisher='''''Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas'''''|pages=Objectives|language=en|doi=|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bsp.gov.ph%2Fabout%2Ffunctions.asp&date=2014-07-05|archivedate=2014-07-05|quote=|deadurl=yes}}</ref>
=== 职能 ===
菲律宾中央银行为完成其法定目标，依法承担之职能有<ref name="Functions"></ref>：
*流动资金管理：制定与执行[[货币政策|货币政策]]之目的是影响[[货币供应量|货币供应量]]，从而维持[[物价|物价]]稳定；
*[[货币发行|货币发行]]：独占国家[[法定货币|法定货币]]之发行权力；
*[[最后贷款人|最后贷款人]]：帮助出现资金流转危机的银行,并为其提供紧急贷款；
*[[金融机构|金融监管]]：监管[[商业银行|商业银行]]与非银行[[金融机构|金融机构]]的业务活动；
*[[外汇储备|外汇储备管理]]：维持并管理足够的[[外汇储备|外汇储备]]，以维护[[菲律宾比索|菲律宾比索]]的稳定性；
*[[汇率政策|汇率政策实施]]：坚持以市场为导向的汇率政策；
*其他活动包括：作为银行家，担任政府的财政顾问，保管政府税收等。

== 组织架构 ==
===行政管理===
菲律宾央行之最高管理机构为'''货币委员会'''（Monetary Board），委员会依法应由七人组成且全部由[[菲律宾总统|总统]]任命，其任期为六年且不能连任<ref name="buxulianren">{{harvnb|《The New Central Bank Act(RA 7653)》|1993|loc=Chapter I：Article II：Section 6}}{{quote|''Composition of the Monetary Board.'' _ The powers and functions of the Bangko Sentral shall be exercised by the Bangko Sentral Monetary Board, hereafter referred to as the Monetary Board, composed of seven (7) members appointed by the President of the Philippines for a term of six (6) years.}}</ref><ref name="Mboard">{{Cite web|url=http://www.bsp.gov.ph/about/governance_mon.asp|title=The Monetary Board of BSP|accessdate=2014-12-08|author=|last=|first=|authorlink=|coauthors=|date=|year=|month=|format=|work=|publisher='''''Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas'''''|pages=|language=en|doi=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140831105153/http://www.bsp.gov.ph/about/governance_mon.asp|archivedate=2014-08-31|quote='''S1'''：The powers and function of Bangko Sentral are exercised by its Monetary Board, which has seven members appointed by the President of The Philippines. Under the New Central Bank Act, one of the government sector members of the Monetary Board must also be a member of the Cabinet designated by the President.the Governor and the other members of the Monetary Board serve terms of six years and may only be removed for cause. '''S2'''：The BSP Monetary Board: Chairman: Amando M. Tetangco, Jr.. Members: Cesar V. Purisima, Alfredo C. Antonio, Juan D. De Zuñiga, Jr., Valentin A. Araneta, Felipe M. Medalla, Armando L. Suratos.|deadurl=yes}}</ref>{{rp|s1}}。央行行长为委员会之当然主席，而主席以下的其他成员包括一名{{link-en|菲律宾内阁|Cabinet of the Philippines|内阁}}驻行委员，及五名来自私营部门且不兼任公职的全职委员<ref name="zgrmyh"></ref>。
委员会之下由行长主管[[行政管理|行政管理]]事务，负责领导各副行长处理执行性事务。{{sfn |《BSP Annual Report 2013》|2014|loc=p.Ⅺ}}
